        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-26T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-26T20:00:00-05:00" n="300" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.00/10–1945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-26T20:00:00-05:00">October 26, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1517. Preliminary replies from the other American Govts regarding consultation on
                    the Argentine situation emphasize the opinion of many of them that no action
                    should be taken pending the completion of consultation. Views expressed in
                    Deptel 1488, Oct 23, must, of course, be taken in conjunction with our
                    established policy of consultation and of multilateral approach to the whole
                    Argentine problem. The fact remains that it is the Argentine people themselves
                    who are responsible in the last analysis for the solution of their political
                    problems.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
